// Extract quarter and year from the date column
val catheter = catheter_ds

import org.apache.spark.sql.{SparkSession, functions => F}
import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window

// Create a Spark session
val spark = SparkSession.builder.appName("Revenue_Analysis").getOrCreate()

// Filter data for markets outside the US and specific quarters
val us_customers = catheter_ds.filter((catheter_ds("country") === "US") && catheter_ds("actual_first_shipped_quarter").isin("2022 Q 2", "2023 Q 2"))

// Group revenue by customer and period
val revenue_by_customer_period = us_customers.groupBy("customer_name", "actual_first_shipped_quarter")
    .agg(F.sum("revenue").alias("revenue_sum"))
    .groupBy("customer_name")
    .pivot("actual_first_shipped_quarter")
    .agg(F.first("revenue_sum"))

// Calculate revenue growth or decline with handling nulls
val revenue_by_customer_period_with_growth = revenue_by_customer_period
    .withColumn("2022 Q 2", F.coalesce(F.col("2022 Q 2"), F.lit(0)))
    .withColumn("2023 Q 2", F.coalesce(F.col("2023 Q 2"), F.lit(0)))
    .withColumn("growth", F.col("2023 Q 2") - F.col("2022 Q 2"))

// Rank customers by growth or decline
val windowSpec_growth = Window.orderBy(F.col("growth").desc)
val windowSpec_decline = Window.orderBy(F.col("growth"))

val revenue_by_customer_period_with_ranks = revenue_by_customer_period_with_growth
    .withColumn("rank_growth", F.rank.over(windowSpec_growth))
    .withColumn("rank_decline", F.rank.over(windowSpec_decline))

// Get top twenty customers with revenue growth
val top_growth_customers = revenue_by_customer_period_with_ranks.filter(F.col("rank_growth") <= 20)
    .orderBy(F.col("growth").desc)

// Get top twenty customers with revenue decline
val top_decline_customers = revenue_by_customer_period_with_ranks.filter(F.col("rank_decline") <= 20)
    .orderBy("growth")

// Display top twenty customers with revenue growth
println("Top Twenty Accounts in the US showing Revenue Growth Q2 2023 vs Q2 2022:")
top_growth_customers.show()

// Display top twenty customers with revenue decline
println("\nTop Twenty Accounts in the US showing Revenue Decline Q2 2023 vs Q2 2022:")
top_decline_customers.show()

// start by importing libraries
import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window

// Create a Spark session
val spark = SparkSession.builder.appName("TopAccountsPerQuarter").getOrCreate()

// Load the data
val catheter_ds = spark.read.format("csv").option("delimiter", ",").option("header", true).option("inferSchema", true).option("mode", "MALFORMED").load("catheter_shipments_revised.csv")

// Group revenue by item and period
val revenue_by_item_period = catheter_ds.groupBy("item", "actual_first_shipped_quarter")
    .agg(F.sum("revenue").alias("revenue_sum"))
    .groupBy("item")
    .pivot("actual_first_shipped_quarter")
    .agg(F.first("revenue_sum"))

val revenue_by_item_period_with_growth = revenue_by_item_period
    .na.fill(0, revenue_by_item_period.columns.filter(_.startsWith("20"))) // Replace nulls in quarter columns starting with "20" with zeros
    .withColumn("growth", F.col("2023 Q 3") - F.col("2021 Q 1")) // Calculate growth
    .na.fill(0, Seq("growth")) // Replace null growth values with zeros


// Find top items contributing to revenue growth
val top_growth_items = revenue_by_item_period_with_growth
    .orderBy(F.col("growth").desc)
    .limit(20) // Get the top 20 items

val formatted_growth_items = top_growth_items
    .withColumn("growth_formatted", format_number(col("growth"), 2))
    .select(
        col("item"),
        col("2021 Q 1"),
        col("2023 Q 3"),
        col("growth_formatted").alias("growth")
    )

// Display top items contributing to revenue growth with formatted growth column
println("Top Items Contributing to Revenue Growth (Formatted):")
formatted_growth_items.show()
